
Directions for connecting the laptop to the new REV hub without cable

1. Plug in a battery to the REV hub so that it is powered and on
2. Wait for the REV hubs light to turn green - this may take a minute or so
3. Once it turns green go to your laptop and connect to the hotspot set up by the drive-a-bot
4. If it asks for a password type password
5. You might have to push the button on the REV hub for it to actually connect
6. Go to the FTC driver station app and set the connection type to control hub
7. Open command prompt and type adb connect 192.168.43.1:5555 then press enter
8. To check if the connection has been established press the green play button and the device should show up as REV hub

